redirect">Karl Raimund Popper</a> in his WWII treatise, <i id="mwB1w">The Open Society and its Enemies</i> (1943).</span></li><li about="#cite_note-167" id="cite_note-167"><a href="./Democracy#cite_ref-167" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-167" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation news" about="#mwt614" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite news","href":"./Template:Cite_news"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/7671283.stm"},"work":{"wt":"BBC News"},"title":{"wt":"Head to head: African democracy"},"date":{"wt":"16 October 2008"},"accessdate":{"wt":"1 April 2010"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB10"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/africa/7671283.stm" id="mwB14">"Head to head: African democracy"</a>. <i id="mwB18">BBC News</i>. 16 October 2008<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwB2A">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwB2E">1 April</span> 2010</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=BBC+News&amp;rft.atitle=Head+to+head%3A+African+democracy&amp;rft.date=2008-10-16&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F1%2Fhi%2Fworld%2Fafrica%2F7671283.stm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADemocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt614" id="mwB2I"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt614" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB2M"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-168" id="cite_note-168"><a href="./Democracy#cite_ref-168" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-168" class="mw-reference-text"><i id="mwB2Q">The Review of Policy Research, Volume 22, Issues 1–3</i