t653" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal ","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Glaeser"},"first1":{"wt":"E."},"last2":{"wt":"Ponzetto"},"first2":{"wt":"G."},"last3":{"wt":"Shleifer"},"first3":{"wt":"A."},"year":{"wt":"2007"},"title":{"wt":"Why does democracy need education?"},"url":{"wt":"http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HUL.InstRepos:27867132"},"journal":{"wt":"Journal of Economic Growth"},"volume":{"wt":"12"},"issue":{"wt":"2"},"pages":{"wt":"77–99"},"doi":{"wt":"10.1007/s10887-007-9015-1"},"access-date":{"wt":"3 July 2017"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB6U">Glaeser, E.; Ponzetto, G.; Shleifer, A. (2007). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HUL.InstRepos:27867132" id="mwB6Y">"Why does democracy need education?"</a>. <i id="mwB6c">Journal of Economic Growth</i>. <b id="mwB6g">12</b> (2): 77–99. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwB6k">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1007%2Fs10887-007-9015-1" id="mwB6o">10.1007/s10887-007-9015-1</a><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwB6s">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwB6w">3 July</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Economic+Growth&amp;rft.atitle=Why+does+democracy+need+education%3F&amp;rft.volume=12&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=77-99&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1007%2Fs10887-007-9015-1&amp;rft.aulast=Glaeser&amp;rft.aufirst=E.&amp;rft.au=Ponzetto%2C+G.&amp;rft.au=Shleifer%2C+A.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnrs.harvard.edu%2Furn-3%3AHUL.InstRepos%3A27867132&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADemocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt653" id="mwB60"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt653" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB64"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-179" id="cite_note-179"><a href="./Democracy#cite_ref-179" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-179" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt655" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal ","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Deary"},"first1":{"wt":"I.J."},"last2":{"wt":"Batty"},"first2":{"wt":"G.D."},"last3":{"wt":"Gale"},"first3":{"wt":"C.R."},"year":{"wt":"2008"},"title":{"wt":"Bright children become enlightened adults"},"url":{"wt":"https://www.pure.ed.ac.uk/ws/files/8896064/bright_children_become_enlightened_adults.pdf"},"journal":{"wt":"Psychological Science"},"volume":{"wt":"19"},"issue":{"wt":"1"},"pages":{"wt":"1–6"},"doi":{"wt":"10.1111/j.1467-9280.2008.02036.x"},"pmid":{"wt":"18181782"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB68">Deary, I.J.; Batty, G.D.; Gale, C.R. (2008). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://www.pure.ed.ac.uk/ws/files/8896064/bright_children_become_enlightened_adults.pdf" id="mwB7A">"Bright children become enlightened adults"</a> <span class="cs1-format" id="mwB7E">(PDF)</span>. <i id="mwB7I">Psychological Science</i>. <b id="mwB7M">19</b> (1): 1–6. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwB7Q">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1111%2Fj.1467-9280.2008.02036.x" id="mwB7U">10.1111/j.1467-9280.2008.02036.x</a>. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./PubMed_Identifier" title="PubMed Identifier" id="mwB7Y" class="mw-redirect">PMID</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwB7c"> </span><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18181782" id="mwB7g">18181782</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Psychological+Science&amp;rft.atitle=Bright+children+become+enlightened+adults&amp;rft.volume=19&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=1-6&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1467-9280.2008.02036.x&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F18181782&amp;rft.aulast=Deary&amp;rft.aufirst=I.J.&amp;rft.au=Batty%2C+G.D.&amp;rft.au=Gale%2C+C.R.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pure.ed.ac.uk%2Fws%2Ffiles%2F8896064%2Fbright_children_become_enlightened_adults.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADemocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt655" id="mwB7k"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt655" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB7o"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-180" id="cite_note-180"><a href="./Democracy#cite_ref-180" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-180" class="mw-reference-text">Compare: <cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt656" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal ","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Rindermann"},"first1":{"wt":"H"},"year":{"wt":"2008"},"title":{"wt":"Relevance of education and intelligence for the political development of nations: Democracy, rule of law and political liberty"},"url":{"wt":""},"journal":{"wt":"Intelligence"},"volume":{"wt":"36"},"issue":{"wt":"4"},"pages":{"wt":"306–22"},"doi":{"wt":"10.1016/j.intell.2007.09.003"},"quote":{"wt":"Political theory has described a positive linkage between education, cognitive ability and democracy. This assumption is confirmed by positive correlations between education, cognitive ability, and positively valued political conditions (N = 183 − 130). [...] It is shown that in the second half of the 20th century, education and intelligence had a strong positive impact on democracy, rule of law and political liberty independent from wealth (GDP) and chosen country sample. One possible mediator of these relationships is the attainment of higher stages of moral judgment fostered by cognitive ability, which is necessary for the function of democratic rules in society. The other mediators for citizens as well as for leaders could be the increased competence and willingness to process and seek information necessary for political decisions due to greater cognitive ability. There are also weaker and less stable reverse effects of the rule of law and political freedom on cognitive ability."}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB7s">Rindermann, H (2008). "Relevance of education and intelligence for the political development of nations: Democracy, rule of law and political liberty". <i id="mwB7w">Intelligence</i>. <b id="mwB70">36</b> (4): 306–22. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwB74">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.intell.2007.09.003" id="mwB78">10.1016/j.intell.2007.09.003</a>. <q id="mwB8A">Political theory has described a positive linkage between education, cognitive ability and democracy. This assumption is confirmed by positive correlations between education, cognitive ability, and positively valued political conditions (N = 183 − 130). [...] It is shown that in the second half of the 20th century, education and intelligence had a strong positive impact on democracy, rule of law and political liberty independent from wealth (GDP) and chosen country sample. One possible mediator of these relationships is the attainment of higher stages of moral judgment fostered by cognitive ability, which is necessary for the function of democratic rules in society. The other mediators for citizens as well as for leaders could be the increased competence and willingness to process and seek information necessary for political decisions due to greater cognitive ability. There are also weaker and less stable reverse effects of the rule of law and political freedom on cognitive ability.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Intelligence&amp;rft.atitle=Relevance+of+education+and+intelligence+for+the+political+development+of+nations%3A+Democracy%2C+rule+of+law+and+political+liberty&amp;rft.volume=36&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=306-22&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.intell.2007.09.003&amp;rft.aulast=Rindermann&amp;rft.aufirst=H&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADemocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt656" id="mwB8E"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt656" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB8I"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-181" id="cite_note-181"><a href="./Democracy#cite_ref-181" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-181" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt771" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal ","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Albertus"},"first1":{"wt":"Michael"},"first2":{"wt":"Victor"},"last2":{"wt":"Menaldo"},"title":{"wt":"Coercive Capacity and the Prospects for Democratisation"},"journal":{"wt":"Comparative Politics"},"volume":{"wt":"44"},"issue":{"wt":"2"},"year":{"wt":"2012"},"pages":{"wt":"151–69"},"doi":{"wt":"10.5129/001041512798838003"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB8M">Albertus, Michael; Menaldo, Victor (2012). "Coercive Capacity and the Prospects for Democratisation". <i id="mwB8Q">Comparative Politics</i>. <b id="mwB8U">44</b> (2): 151–69. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier" id="mwB8Y">doi</a>:<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.5129%2F001041512798838003" id="mwB8c">10.5129/001041512798838003</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Comparative+Politics&amp;rft.atitle=Coercive+Capacity+and+the+Prospects+for+Democratisation&amp;rft.volume=44&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=151-69&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.5129%2F001041512798838003&amp;rft.aulast=Albertus&amp;rft.aufirst=Michael&amp;rft.au=Menaldo%2C+Victor&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADemocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt771" id="mwB8g"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt771" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB8k"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-182" id="cite_note-182"><a href="./Democracy#cite_ref-182" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-182" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt772" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.plawlotic.com/?p=8"},"title":{"wt":"The Resource Curse: Does the Emperor Have no Clothes?"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB8o"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.plawlotic.com/?p=8" id="mwB8s">"The Resource Curse: Does the Emperor Have no Clothes?"</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+Resource+Curse%3A+Does+the+Emperor+Have+no+Clothes%3F&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.plawlotic.com%2F%3Fp%3D8&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADemocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt772" id="mwB8w"></span><link rel="mw-dedupli